UPDATE eleve SET nom='Jacques'
WHERE id=12

SELECT c.libelle AS PHXal_libelle, COUNT(*) AS PHXal_count 
FROM `classe` c
INNER JOIN `eleve` e ON c.id = e.idClasse
WHERE libelle='Terminale'

SELECT c.id AS PHXal_id, e.id AS PHXal_idEleve 
FROM `classe` c
INNER JOIN `eleve` e ON c.id = e.idClasse
ORDER BY e.id

SELECT c.libelle AS PHXal_libelle, COUNT(*) AS PHXal_count 
FROM `classe` c
INNER JOIN `eleve` e ON c.id = e.idClasse
WHERE libelle='Terminale'
